# Task #146: Tried FAST_OUTPUT_REGISTER on DRAM_* outputs and
# FAST_OUTPUT_ENABLE_REGISTER on DRAM_DQ to give clean I/O-cell-
# placed flops with consistent Tco. On silicon this made the FIRST
# master_write_32 hang — the I/O register on DRAM_DQ delays the
# write data by one cycle relative to the WRITE command that the
# chip latches on the same edge, so the chip captured stale DQ.
# Reverted; the controller's writes work correctly with combinational
# DRAM_DQ output (chip's setup/hold margin at 40 MHz absorbs the
# Tco variance). Future work: if we re-enable I/O-cell DQ output
# registers, also bump the chip's sample cycle in 'sdrWriteCmd'
# to issue the data one cycle BEFORE the WRITE command so the
# delays align — but that's a more invasive FSM change.
